<p><b>SPICE</b> (Simulation Program with Integrated Circuit Emphasis) is a general-purpose <a href="/wiki/Analogue_electronics" title="Analogue electronics">analog electronic circuit</a> <a href="/wiki/Electronic_circuit_simulation" title="Electronic circuit simulation">simulator</a>. It is a powerful program that is used in <a href="/wiki/Integrated_circuit" title="Integrated circuit">IC</a> and board-level design to check the integrity of <a href="/wiki/Circuit_design" title="Circuit design">circuit designs</a> and to predict <a href="/wiki/Electronic_circuit" title="Electronic circuit">circuit</a> behavior.</p>
